      "title": "ℹ️ About — BrainDead FaceWrap",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# FaceWrap Pipeline — photo views → clean UV face texture\n\nTurns a **4-view head photo stack** (front / left / right / rear) into a single seamless **UV face texture** you can drop onto CC5 / MetaHuman / canonical heads. MediaPipe finds the landmarks, the canonical (or ICT) face mesh is fit to them, each view is baked into UV space, then all views are confidence-blended into one texture with a gap (inpaint) mask.\n\n## Flow\n1. **Load Image** — a batched image: front, left, right, rear (that order).\n2. **BD Face Landmarks** — MediaPipe FaceLandmarker → 478 landmarks per view (+ overlay).\n3. **BD Face Fit** — fits the canonical / ICT head mesh to the landmark stack.\n4. **BD Face Texture Bake** — projects every view into the shared UV layout (textures + confidences).\n5. **BD UV Confidence Blend** — cosine-weighted composite → one UV texture + filled / inpaint masks.\n6. **Preview Image** — the finished blended UV texture.\n\nThe `inpaint_mask` output of the blend feeds a Qwen Image Edit step (see **BD Face Wrap Composite**) to fill the remaining gaps — omitted here to keep the template model-free.\n\n## Models / VRAM\n`BD Face Landmarks` downloads `face_landmarker.task` (MediaPipe, ~3 MB) to the mediapipe model dir on first run. The canonical / ICT face meshes are bundled with the node pack. No checkpoint / diffusion model needed — runs on CPU-to-low VRAM. Provide your own 4-view head batch via Load Image.\n\n---\n**BrainDeadGuild** — created by **BizaNator**\n[BrainDeadGuild.com](https://BrainDeadGuild.com) · [BrainDead.TV](https://BrainDead.TV) · [GitHub](https://github.com/BizaNator/ComfyUI-BrainDead) · [Discord](https://braindeadguild.com/discord)\n"
      ]
    },
